[DhtmlXQ_comment0]eg xqsycj tjm 102 1c1hp1a2e sw 2a2e||||In the endgame, the combination of 1c1hp1a2e would be a sure win against a full guard.||However, three points must be taken note off:||1) the pawn MUST NEVER advance reckelessly. Instead, it should bide his time to capture the opponent's advisors/elephants for free.||2) the pawn can also be used in exchange for two elephants as the endgame would also be simplified to a sure win for red too. (1c1a sw 2a)||3) the king is required for the assist.||||10 endgames are shown here, eight of which will be positional wins.||Jim : A basic, must learn endgame![/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
